Title: Flat earther accidently proves earth’s rotation with $ 20k gyro. That’s kind of a problem, right?
Description:
All rights belong to Netflix, no copyright infringement intended. In the documentary “Beyond the curve”, a flat earther is unhappy with his measurements of earth’s rotation.

Flat earther Bob's problems with his measurement of earth's rotation: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SVvf617ReVs
Flat earther Jeran's problems with his detection of earth's curvature: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RapVrOQwv8o
Of course, both flat earthers claim that the documentary was deceptive. Of course, they've both lied when making up excuses. See this analysis from Sly Sparkane: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nW_lIPdsWjY
See how Bob Knodel was exposed lying about his flight license: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JjqOzimCz7A

If you are a flat earther: nope, the earth is not flat! You can clearly see the curvature in undistorted (!) amateur footage:
https://imgur.com/a/vGrZssA
https://imgur.com/a/RacViFN
Since the curvature is consistent, regardless of the camera's angle, it's proved that the curvature is not due to a fisheye lens. The overlay shows the theoretical expectation on a sphere with earth's radius, calculated with Walti’s horizon app: http://walter.bislins.ch/bloge/index.asp?page=Flat%2DEarth%3A+Finding+the+Curvature+of+the+Earth
The observation and the expectation match very well.
